<H3> <TI>   Donations From Galician Organizations Arrive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Donations From Galician Organizations Arrive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0906223894 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1955 GMT 
9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0906223894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Food staples, medicine, school supplies, and medical 
equipment donated to Cuba by various Galician friendship 
organizations arrived on 9 June at the Port of Havana from Vigo, 
Spain. The 37-ton shipment was brought to Cuba by the Rio 
Jibacoa, a fishing vessel 106 meters in overall length, and with 
3,200-ton displacement. 
  Jose Ramon Fernandez, vice president of the Council of 
Ministers, was in attendance to receive the donation sent by the 
associations' Francisco Villamil, Carballino, Bartolome de las 
Casas, Gomez de Millan, the Galician autonomous government, and 
the Red Cross. Tomas Gonzalez Ramirez, captain of the Rio 
Jibacoa, explained that besides the Galician donation, the 
vessel also carried another donation consisting of 23 packages, 
mainly medicine, from the Spanish port of Alicante. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

