<H3> <TI>   Minister Hails `Firm' OAS Message on Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Hails `Firm' OAS Message on Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0906184494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0906184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Claudette Werleigh, the Aristide government's 
foreign minister, considers the latest OAS General Assembly 
measure a very firm message to the de facto authorities in 
Haiti. The 34 OAS foreign ministers adopted a resolution on an 
embargo on commercial flights to and from Haiti and on freezing 
the financial assets of members of the Haitian provisional 
government: 
  [Begin Werleigh recording, in Creole] This is why they 
mention in the resolution....[pauses] One of the last points 
involves working toward professionalizing the Army so that we 
can have an Army that protects the territory and helps us form 
the new police force provided for in our Constitution rather 
than one that tortures people, kills, and destroys. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

