<H3> <TI>   Aristide Accused of High Treason </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aristide Accused of High Treason </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0906205694 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0906205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Capois-La-Mort Organization has accused the 
president-in-exile of the crime of high treason and of 
complicity with the enemy. The organization calls on the Senate 
of the Republic to rigorously apply the Constitution to its 
maximum against Jean-Bertrand Aristide, accusing him of having 
asked, on several occasions, for the occupation of his own 
country by a foreign Army. 
  The Capois-La-Mort Organization demands the government set 
in 
motion public action against the president-in-exile, guilty, 
according to the organization, of high treason and complicity 
with the enemy. 
  The National Christian Democratic Party, PDCH, reasserts its 
opposition to the physical return of President Aristide to Haiti 
and expresses indignation about the latest statements by the 
priest/president. PDCH calls those statements murderous. PDCH of 
the late Sylvio Claude, led by Joachin Pierre, asks the 
concerned institutions, especially the Haitian parliament, to 
assume their responsibilities lest the institutions be 
questioned in the court of history. 

</TEXT>

