<H3> <TI>   Army Responsibility for Detention Centers Ended </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Responsibility for Detention Centers Ended </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0906222194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1800 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0906222194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government of Judge Emile Jonassaint has decided 
to release the Haitian Armed Forces from managing detention 
centers. Following a meeting of the Council of Ministers at the 
National Palace and a follow-up visit by the ministerial 
delegation to the national penitentiary, the government of the 
provisional president has decided to put the management of the 
detention centers in the hands of civilian authorities. 
Meanwhile, the provisional government points out that prompt 
measures to improve the conditions of the prisoners will be 
taken. 

</TEXT>

