<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sources close to some of the diplomatic missions in 
Port-au-Prince are reporting that some foreign nationals have 
allegedly begun leaving the country in light of a possible armed 
intervention. Members of international and nongovernmental 
organizations working in the country could start leaving on 10 
June on the recommendation of their respective countries. Some 
meetings have been held on this issue, but no public notice has 
been issued yet. 

