<H3> <TI>   Profits of Ammunition, Oil, Gas Industries Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Profits of Ammunition, Oil, Gas Industries Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0906144894 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 8 
Jun 94 p B6 </F>

<F P=103> PY0906144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Carlos Franco] </F>
  [Excerpts] The weapons and ammunition industry increased 
significantly last year, recovering its $1.5 million loss in 
1992, attaining a net profit of $8.4 million in 1993. Sales, 
especially those of the Brazilian Cartridge Company [Companhia 
Brasileira de Cartuchos] (CBC) jumped from $98.8 million in 1992 
to $143.2 million in 1993, that is, a 44.9 percent increase. 
[passage omitted] 
  The oil and gas industries, which include Petrobras 
[Brazilian Petroleum Corporation] distributors, closed 1993 with 
net sales of $22.6 billion and net profits of $858.9 million. 
Profits obtained in 1993 were 194 percent up on the $292.4 
million profit obtained in 1992. 

</TEXT>

