<F P=106> [Article by Joao Baptista Natali] </F>
  [Excerpts] The 170 or so radio stations linked to the 
Catholic Church will, next January, begin joint transmissions of 
part of their programs. 
  They will transmit through the Igreja-Sat distribution 
system 
operated by Brasil-Sat (Brazilian Satellite Telecommunications). 
  The system will use the satellite channel that was utilized 
by Radio Aparecida, from Apareida do Norte (Sao Paulo). 
  The decision to install a Catholic radio broadcasting 
network 
was quietly made in April, during a general assembly of CNBB 
(National Conference of Brazilian Bishops). 
  On 23 April, bishops and advisers of the Igreja-Sat 
Executive 
Group decided to create a foundation to manage the radio system 
[passage omitted] 
  Father Cesar Moreira was designated president of the 
Igreja-Sat system. He also heads Unda (wave, in Latin), a 
church organization linked with electronic media. [passage 
omitted] 

