<H3> <TI>   Franco's Agrarian Reform Efforts Surpass Collor's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Franco's Agrarian Reform Efforts Surpass Collor's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0806152294 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 7 
Jun 94 p 6 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY0806152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From Ronaldo Brasiliense's column: "JB Report"] </F>
  [Text] President Itamar Franco already has surpassed 
Fernando Collor by far in terms of agrarian reform. 
  In his 31 months in office, Collor expropriated only 20,000 
hectares of land and assisted 494 families. 
  During the Itamar Franco administration, 763,000 hectares 
have been expropriated and 19,000 families of landless rural 
workers assisted. 

</TEXT>

