<H3> <TI>   OAS General Assembly Continues Brazil Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    OAS General Assembly Continues Brazil Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Dominican Opposition Not Allowed To Speak </H4>

<F P=102> PY1006134594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1936 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1006134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belem, 9 Jun (EFE) -- A mission representing 
Dominican President Joaquin Balaguer today foiled an attempt by 
opponents to Balaguer's government to raise electoral fraud 
charges against him at the plenum of the 24th OAS General 
Assembly, which is slated to close on 10 June. 
  A delegation of Balaguer's political opponents led by vice 
presidential candidate Fernando Alvarez Bogaert has 
unsuccessfully tried to participate in the OAS assembly -- which 
is being held at the city of Belem, Para State -- through an 
invitation extended to them by a Central American country, 
possibly Costa Rica. 
  The attempt was rejected by most of the 34 delegates, who 
centered their efforts on the Haitian crisis and the 
strengthening of the trade embargo to force the ouster of the 
"de facto" Haitian Government, thanks to behind-the-scenes 
negotiations conducted by Dominican Foreign Minister Juan 
Taveras and other Balaguer envoys. 
  Mario Read-Bitti, president of the Dominican Republic 
Central 
Bank, told EFE: "It is surprising that the opposition attempted 
to raise a domestic subject here that concerns only the 
Dominican people." 
  When it became clear that Alvarez would not be able to speak 
at the OAS plenum, the opposition mission sought to propose a 
draft resolution in which the OAS voices concern about the 
openness of the vote count conducted by the Dominican Central 
Electoral Board. 
  Diplomatic sources told EFE that although this initiative 
also failed OAS Secretary General Joao Baena Soares may refer to 
the Dominican elections in his closing speech on 10 June. 
  The OAS had sent a mission of observers to oversee the 
recent 
elections in Dominican Republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-33777 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat113bb_94006" </HT>


