<H3> <TI>   CPC Delegation Tours Cienfuegos Energy Plants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CPC Delegation Tours Cienfuegos Energy Plants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1106110194 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1106110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Text] The CPC delegation headed by Wu Banggou, Politburo 
member and CPC secretary in Shanghai, has visited Cienfuegos 
Province. The delegation was greeted at the local government's 
headquarters by Manuel Menendez Castellano, member of the 
Central Committee and first secretary of the Communist Party of 
Cuba [PCC] in the province, and other provincial authorities. 
  The delegation toured the Camilo Cienfuegos Refinery during 
a 
visit to the industrial park. The refinery is nearly completed 
and has already been producing for the last three years. The 
plant could benefit from an investment that would increase its 
efficiency. The delegation also visited the Juragua Nuclear 
Plant, where they were told that construction is temporarily 
halted but that the facility has been preserved. The delegation 
was also informed that negotiations recently got underway to 
form an economic association that will make it possible to 
complete the plant and start operations. 
  The delegation also met higher education teachers and 
students in the province. The delegation will visit Matanzas 
Province on 11 June and is scheduled to depart Cuba on 12 June. 
  This is the highest ranking PRC delegation to visit Cuba 
since Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit. 

</TEXT>

