<HT>    "drlat113_a_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-113 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits Hotel, Oil Fields in Matanzas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits Hotel, Oil Fields in Matanzas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1306003594 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1306003594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Text] Wu Banggou, CPC Politburo member and CPC secretary 
general in Shanghai, appeared to be very happy with his visit to 
Cuba, which continued this afternoon in Matanzas Province. Wu 
Banggou and his delegation were accompanied by Politburo member 
Yadira Garcia, first secretary of the party in Matanzas 
Province, on a tour during which they learned of the 
developments in the tourist and oil industry programs. At the 
Melia Varadero Hotel, the delegation was informed of the profits 
made by this and other joint capital enterprises, as well as the 
basis and characteristics for this type of business. 
  Cuba's largest producing oil field lies near Varadero Beach. 
The oil field's workers have an annual production goal of 
930,000 tons, nearly 75 percent of Cuba's production goal. Work 
is aimed at surpassing this goal. Wu Banggou was informed of 
the joint operations with Canadian and French companies and the 
progress in the program designed to increase production and 
explore the possibilities of new drilling areas. 
  In an interview for this newscast, Wu Banggou stressed the 
need to strengthen economic cooperation between Cuba and the PRC 
even more. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

