<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Text] Politburo members Jose Ramon Balaguer and Carlos 
Lage bid farewell to the CPC delegation at Jose Marti Airport on 
12 June. Wu Banngou said he was very satisfied with his visit to 
Cuba and underscored the importance of having met President 
Fidel Castro on two occasions. In a statement for Cuban 
television, he said: 
  [Begin Wu recording in Mandarin with passage by passage 
translation into Spanish] We are greatly impressed with some 
things. Cuba made it through 1993, a most difficult year. Cuba 
now has a very clear development strategy. Cuba has adopted a 
series of achievable economic measures. We sincerely hope that 
Cuba can continue developing every day. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

