<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] Army General Raul Castro continues to tour the 
Central Army region. On this occasion he visited areas of the 
Victoria de Giron Citrus Enterprise in Jaguey Grande, Matanzas 
Province. Raul and his companions visited farm number 2 of 
Jaguey's citrus program. The delegation held a meeting with 
Agriculture Minister Alfredo Jordan, member of the Politburo; 
provincial party leaders, enterprise managers; and the general 
staff of the 102d Division of the Youth Labor Army [EJT]. 
  In the meeting, an agreement was reached to incoporate 
citrus 
plantations into EJT farms, which have already demonstrated 
their efficiency in this region and other parts of Cuba. The 
EJT already manages six of the 10 farms of the enterprise, the 
remaining four will be put under EJT control later in the year. 
[passage omitted]. 

