<F P=102>   FL1106170894 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1106170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New reactions have been recorded in Haiti following 
the U.S. sanctions. On 10 June, Port-au-Prince Mayor-elect 
Evans Paul asked General Raoul Cedras, head of the Haitian Army, 
to resign to avoid the application of the new sanctions 
announced on the same day by U.S. President Bill Clinton. The 
basis of the solution to avoid those new sanctions, which are 
very hard and very painful and which hit all Haitians, remains 
the implementation of the Governors Island agreement, Paul 
pointed out. Gen. Cedras must understand the necessity to 
respect his commitment, he added. 
  President Clinton announced among other things the 
interdiction of commercial flights between the United States and 
Haiti as of 25 June and the suspension of private financial 
transactions with Haiti. 

