<H3> <TI>   FG, Socialist Unity Blocs Walk Out </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FG, Socialist Unity Blocs Walk Out </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1006183794 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2201 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1006183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Grand Front [FG] and Socialist Unity [US] blocs 
carried out their threat to walk out of the Constituent Assembly 
session as the regulations, specifically Article 129, were being 
voted on, and [FG leader] Fernando Solanas resigned his post as 
Constituent Assembly second vice president. Thus, the FG and US 
blocs expressed their repudiation of the approval of an article 
in the regulations indicating that the Nucleus of Basic 
Agreements must be voted on as a whole and not point by point, 
as repeatedly requested by the opposition. 
  The provincial parties and Movement for Dignity and 
Independence blocs, which also are challenging the regulations 
proposed by the majority, decided to remain in the Constituent 
Assembly meeting and vote against the regulations. 

</TEXT>

