<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 10 Jun (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
today issued precise instructions to Defense Minister Oscar 
Camilion to "quickly eliminate the compulsory recruitment 
service and implement an entirely professional Armed Forces." 
  This was reported by the head of state, who unexpectedly 
asked reporters waiting outside the Olivos residence to enter 
the residence's main chalet, where the president was meeting 
with his ministers. 
  Menem interrupted the meeting to release the news, and then 
boarded a helicopter to travel to the northern dock of the 
metropolitan port to preside over a farewell ceremony for the 
training ship Fragata Libertad. 
  "We will report future steps in time. The Defense Ministry 
has instructions to take the appropriate measures, together with 
the military commanders and authorities, to fulfill what the 
president said," Menem added. 

