<H3> <TI>   'Controversy' Over Generals' Meeting Overcome </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Controversy' Over Generals' Meeting Overcome </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1106013794 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1800 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1106013794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jorge Schaulsohn, president of the Chamber of 
Deputies, considers the controversy provoked by a meeting of the 
corps of Army generals to be resolved. 
  On 1 June, the Army leaked information that Deputy Army 
Commander General Jorge Lucar summoned the corps of generals to 
assess the comments of Socialist Deputy Jaime Naranjo, who 
referred to General Augusto Pinochet's trip to Europe. He said 
the demonstrations against Pinochet show the world still 
remembers the crimes he committed. 
  Schaulsohn held a meeting with Defense Minister Edmundo 
Perez 
Yoma because he believed the Army high command should not assess 
comments by a legislator. 
  [Begin Schaulsohn recording] If this meeting did really take 
place, Gen. Lucar, whom I highly respect, made a serious mistake 
by calling it. [end recording] 
  Schaulsohn added that the Army was correct in channeling its 
unrest to the defense minister. 
  [Begin Schaulsohn recording] The Army was annoyed by 
comments 
by honorable Deputy Naranjo and Gen. Lucar expressed the Army's 
unrest to the defense minister through the appropriate channel. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

