<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion Leaves 5 Dead, 6 Injured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosion Leaves 5 Dead, 6 Injured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1106162994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1227 GMT 11 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1106162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guadalajara, 11 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- A preliminary toll 
of five dead, six injured, and extensive property damage is the 
result of an explosion outside the Camino Real Hotel in this 
capital city of the Mexican Jalisco State, police authorities 
have reported. 
  The police confirmed that the incident occurred at 0230 in 
the morning (0830 GMT) when a 1993 Ford Grand Marquis car that 
had been loaded with explosives blew up. The vehicle was parked 
in front of the "Camichine" room of the aforementioned hotel. 
  Relief and security offices have reported that the explosion 
destroyed 10 vehicles, including the bus of the "Los Huracanes" 
musical group, and broke the windows of the room where a 
birthday ball was being held to celebrate the 15th birthday of 
Karine Ramirez. 
  Judicial Police Director Roberto Machuca Aguilar commented 
that the party started last night and that the room for the ball 
had been rented by a lady whose last name is Fernandez Castro, 
apparently from Sinaloa State. 
  Of the six people injured, who were sent to different health 
centers, five were identified as Jorge Castro Angulo, Alberto 
Menchado Montes, Arturo Rangel Martinez, Ramon Perez Velarde, 
and Jose Andres Gonzalez Padilla, 38, 30, 46, 34, and 20 years 
of age, respectively. 
  [Paris AFP in Spanish at 1450 GMT on 11 Jun 94 reports from 
Mexico City that "according to local reporters, the car bomb 
could have been placed as an act of vengeance between drug 
trafficking bands that operate in Guadalajara or as retaliation 
for the arrest of Manuel Quintero Payan, related to a powerful 
drug trafficking band." The AFP report adds that reporters have 
linked the arrest of Quintero Payan to the car bomb "because the 
people who attended the girl's birthday party talked like 
`northeners' and thus are associated to the drug trafficking 
bands."] 

</TEXT>

