<H3> <TI>   Authorities Seize Ammunition Shipment to Guerrero </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Seize Ammunition Shipment to Guerrero </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1006160294 Mexico City LA JORNADA in Spanish 9 Jun 94 p 25 </F>
<F P=103> PA1006160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City LA JORNADA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yolanda Gonzalez Gomez] </F>
  [Text] Hermosillo, Sonora State, 8 Jun -- Federal Treasury 
Police agents yesterday seized 10,000 rounds of small-arms 
ammunition of various calibers at the 21-km marker checkpoint in 
Nogales. The ammunition was apparently on its way to Guerrero 
State. 
  The Nogales customs office indicated the seizure was made 
after inspecting a Dodge van bearing Oregon State license 
plates, from where the shipment destined for Guerrero came. 
Hidden inside boxes containing second-hand clothing, tires, and 
home appliances, the authorities discovered 7.62-mm, 9-mm, .38 
super-, .380-, .22-, and .30-caliber cartridges. Javier Chavez 
Rodriguez and Demetrio Goicochea Rodriguez were arrested and 
turned over, along with the shipment, to the Federal 
Prosecutor's Office in Nogales. 

</TEXT>

