<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Argentina Accepts Delay in Filling of Yacyreta Dam </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Argentina Accepts Delay in Filling of Yacyreta Dam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1006170594 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 9 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PY1006170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Argentine Government has accepted a Paraguayan 
proposal to postpone until 16 July the start of filling the 
Yacyreta Dam. This was announced on 8 June at the end of a 
meeting at Government Palace between President Juan Carlos 
Wasmosy, Foreign Minister Luis Maria Ramirez Boettner, and 
Argentine Ambassador Raul Carignano. During this time all 
problems on the Paraguayan side of the river must be solved. 
Carignano said President Wasmosy assured him that the Paraguayan 
Government will guarantee the fulfillment of the treaty schedule 
and that the postponement will not affect the date established 
for the first generator to begin operations -- 1 September. 

</TEXT>

