<H3> <TI>   Endara: Panama To Insist on Cuba's Reentry Into OAS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Endara: Panama To Insist on Cuba's Reentry Into OAS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1106233994 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 11 
Jun 94 p 28 </F>

<F P=103> PA1106233994 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Esteban Huertas] </F>
  [Excerpt] President Guillermo Endara said yesterday that 
"Panama must insist" on Cuba's reentry into the OAS, as has been 
suggested by other countries of the region. 
  Endara said that the Fourth Ibero-American Summit, to take 
place in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia on 14 and 15 June, "will 
not address the Cuban situation." 
  According to Endara, the chiefs of state "have met with 
Castro at other summit meetings, to seek ways to democratize the 
island" and have been unsuccessful for the last 30 years. 
  Whenever the issue is addressed, Endara said, "Castro always 
approaches the discussion in a rational and open way, as the 
dignified and responsible person that he is." 
  The Panamanian leader said he has spoken many times with the 
Cuban statesman, whom he finds to be "an exceptional individual, 
despite the political differences" that separate the two 
presidents. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

