<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosive Device Found in Store Near Miraflores Palace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explosive Device Found in Store Near Miraflores Palace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1206121994 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1206121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] An explosive device was left abandoned this 
afternoon at the Miraflores drug store, located less than 50 
meters from the presidential palace and next to the Weapons and 
Explosives Directorate of the Interior Ministry. According to 
information obtained at the site, someone left a dark brown 
briefcase at approximately 1400, when the drug store is most 
crowded. The store clerks became suspicious and called the 
Directorate of Intelligence and Prevention Services for help. 
Officials from the Weapons and Explosives Directorate arrived 
and took the necessary measures. After x-raying the briefcase, 
they decided to detonate the explosive device. At this time, 
the authorities do not know who is responsible for this new 
terrorist action which could have caused injuries and damage 
near the presidential palace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

