  [Text] Foreign Minister Jose Raul Mulino has stated that 
drugs and illegal drug trafficking are matters that concern both 
the United States and Panama. He added that it is a priority to 
hold a high-level meeting to coordinate joint actions. 
  [Begin Mulino recording] If the U.S. Government confirms it, 
we will hold a meeting at the highest level in Panama during the 
first week of July. I will preside over this meeting, and it is 
to be attended by very important U.S. State and Justice 
Department, perhaps even U.S. Treasury, officials to discuss all 
the drug trafficking and money laundering problems. 
  As you will recall, on 13 April I sent a letter to U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher telling him that, instead 
of talking and arguing whether we have cooperated or not, I 
invited him to a high-level meeting in Panama to discuss this 
topic. The invitation has been accepted and, hopefully, will be 
held during the first week of July. [end recording] 

