<H3> <TI>   Ross, PRC Labor Delegation Tour Research Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ross, PRC Labor Delegation Tour Research Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1006182594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1006182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Doing Radio" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Over 10,000 efficiency assemblies have been held in 
the country, it was stated by CTC [Cuban Workers Federation] 
Secretary General Pedro Ross in a meeting with a delegation of 
the All-China Federation of Trade Unions that is currently 
visiting Cuba. 
  Ross, who is also a member of the Communist Party of Cuba 
[PCC] politburo, explained to the labor union leaders of the 
friendly nation that the assembly process is a result of the 
Cuban workers' decision that labor unions become directly 
involved in the solution of problems at their enterprises in 
particular and the country in general. 
  Ross' statement was given at the Medical Biophysics Research 
Center, a leading institution in Santiago de Cuba's scientific 
sector that is in charge of manufacturing equipment for medical 
diagnoses and research on diseases through the use of nuclear 
magnetic resonance. 
  Xiao Zhenbang, a member of the PRC delegation, congratulated 
the workers for their achievments, and he urged them to continue 
their vital research for the development of the island's 
pharmaceutical and medical industry. 

</TEXT>

