<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Text] Politburo member Jose Ramon Machado Ventura has 
participated in the District 27 progress report assembly in 
Guantanamo City. Machado witnessed an extensive debate with 
considerable participation by the people, who calmly suggested 
many ideas aimed at resolving shortages through local 
alternatives. Machado, who is Guantanamo Municipality's deputy 
to the National Assembly of the People's Government, was briefed 
on the efforts the population is making to recover from the 
recent rains, efforts not only in each neighborhood but also on 
the farms of the Segundo Frente Frank Pais contingent, which 
Machado also visited and praised: 
  [Begin Machado recording] This is heartwarming. Here, you 
can see the disposition and drive with which the people renew 
their work. [end recording] 
  Machado's tour of Guantanamo included an evaluation of a 
great number of Basic Cooperative Production Units, where the 
need to stabilize the work force was emphasized. The suggested 
solutions included improving living conditions, guaranteeing 
cost reductions, and increasing production. 

