<H3> <TI>   Candido Palmero Congratulates Western Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Candido Palmero Congratulates Western Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1306234394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1306234394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Passages within quotations marks recorded] </F>
  [Text] Candido Palmero, first secretary of the Communist 
Party of Cuba in Havana Province, has sent a message of 
congratulations to the members of the Western Army on tomorrow's 
observance of the 33d anniversary of its creation. 
  [Palmero] "They have been a school for training cadres and 
communists. We, just as our people do, greatly admire and 
appreciate them for their revolutionary attitude and exemplary 
commitment to the work of the Revolution in these difficult 
times." 
  Palmero also highlighted the significant support of the 
troops in the province's agriculture. 
  [Palmero] "Approximately 2,000 members -- generals, 
officers, 
soldiers -- conducted the potato harvest, together with the 
Youth Labor Army [EJT]. Over 73 percent of the harvest was 
collected with enormous efficiency. Right now, the EJT is 50 
percent of the entire labor force in the province. They 
successfully complete their tasks with fewer men and more 
efficiency and productivity." 
  Palmero pointed out the influence of the Western Army in the 
combat training of the people in the province. 
  [Palmero] "During these 33 years, this command has done 
wonders for the defense of the Revolution. One of the most 
historic and difficult struggles has been that many of us, a 
great number of the population -- militants, workers, and 
farmers -- fulfilled internationalist missions while in the 
service of the Western Army. Many comrades of this command gave 
their lives in other lands." 

</TEXT>

