<H3> <TI>   Labor Official: $1.7 Million Invested in Social Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Official: $1.7 Million Invested in Social Security </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1306212394 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0000 GMT 11 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1306212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Cuban Panorama" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In 1993, Cuba invested more than $1.7 million in 
social security , some $4 million every 24 hours. [sentence as 
heard] Orlando Penante, social security director of the Cuban 
Labor Ministry, has indicated that those figures do not include 
the costs of social assistance programs, which amount to another 
$35 million. Penante stated that despite the economic hardships 
Cuba is facing, the number of retirees and pensioners covered by 
the social security system has increased in the 50 years of the 
special period in peacetime. The number of subjects covered by 
social security also surpasses the funds allocated for this 
purpose. 

</TEXT>

