<H3> <TI>   Union Issues Electricity Generating Capacity Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Union Issues Electricity Generating Capacity Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1006210494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1006210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Electric Union has issued a detailed report on 
electricity generating capacity, pointing out that increased 
capacity meant shorter outages last week. The Electric Union 
predicts that the system will continue behaving like this until 
15 June. The report also notes that the average deficit was 
reduced significantly between 2 and 8 June and that the 
electrical generating level in the last few weeks has exceeded 
what was expected, increasing consumption of fuel reserved for 
that purpose. 
  The truth is that the situation today is very different from 
that in April, when the outages were prolonged due to breakdowns 
at power plants without adequate maintenance program. The 
generating capacity now increases daily. It was also confirmed 
that Mariel Power Plant Unit 6 has been reincorporated into the 
national electrical network. This unit, which can generate 100 
megawatts, was off line for more than a year while Cuban 
specialists completed their complex reconstruction task. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

