<H3> <TI>   Government Guarantees Security of Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Guarantees Security of Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1406005494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0002 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1406005494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 13 Jun (EFE) -- The de facto 
government of Emile Jonassaint issued a statement today, 
although it is dated Saturday [11 June] and was released a few 
hours after the declaration of the state of emergency throughout 
the country, that it guarantees the security of foreign citizens 
in Haiti. 
  The Information Ministry asked foreigners to carry out their 
normal activities. At the same time, the de facto government 
rejected statements by the international civilian mission of the 
United Nations and the OAS, which charged that employees of the 
international mission were attacked by armed civilians on 7 June. 

</TEXT>

