<F P=102>   PY1306171194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1920 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1306171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 10 Jun (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
this afternoon accepted the resignation tendered by Argentine 
Culture Secretary Jose Maria Castineira de Dios, who will 
reportedly be replaced by writer Jorge Asis. 
  In a brief chat with journalists accredited to the Olivos 
residence, Media Secretary Raul Burzaco said that the president 
had accepted the resignation tendered by Castineira de Dios, and 
offered this post to current Argentine Ambassador to UNESCO 
Jorge Asis. 
  The reasons for the culture secretary's resignation were not 
officially reported. 
  Castineira de Dios' replacement, who is still the Argentine 
ambassador to UNESCO, recently made a public announcement that 
he plans to run in the Buenos Aires Justicialist Party primaries 
for Buenos Aires mayoral candidate in the upcoming elections. 

