<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alleged Shining Path Member Captured in Tucuman City </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alleged Shining Path Member Captured in Tucuman City </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1306183294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1112 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1306183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Miguel de Tucuman, 11 Jun (NA) -- It has been 
officially reported in this city that an alleged member of the 
Peruvian Maoist organization Shining Path was arrested during a 
joint Federal and Tucuman Police operation. The alleged 
terrorist, identified as Jorge Diaz Reategui, was captured at a 
hotel in the poor district of El Bajo, near the city bus 
terminal. At the time of his capture, Reategui was with other 
alleged guerrillas, who managed to escape. 
  Judge Ricardo Maturana is in charge of Federal Court No. 2 
of 
this city. On 10 June he questioned Reategui, but the details 
of the questioning have not been released. 
  Police sources have said Reategui had been under very strict 
surveillance by the Federal Police. 
  It has been suggested that this province is a refugee camp 
for Shining Path members who clandestinely cross the border and 
train Peruvian and Argentine militants who support their 
ideology. 

</TEXT>

