<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Frei Defends Pinochet's European Tour, Ties With Military </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Frei Defends Pinochet's European Tour, Ties With Military </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1406015494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0113 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1406015494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago, 10 Jun (EFE) -- Chilean President Eduardo 
Frei today downplayed criticism of Army Commander Augusto 
Pinochet's recent trip by stating that ties with the Chilean 
Armed Forces are "extraordinarily positive." 
  Ever since his first speeches, Frei has noted the 
"impersonality of power" as a government formula: "In this 
case, there are no personal ties, only institutional ties. 
Government ties with the Armed Forces and their commanders are 
extraordinarily positive." 
  Frei stated that a discussion agenda has been drafted on 
issues the government believes should be defense policy 
guidelines. 
  He said: "General Pinochet made a trip at the institutional 
level. I met with him before his trip and we will assess his 
trip when he returns, as is done with all the Armed Forces 
commanders." 
  Gen. Pinochet's visit to Europe caused protests among some 
European associations, particulary during his stay in the Czech 
Republic. 

</TEXT>

