<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Agreement Signed With Caricom </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1206032494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1206032494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours Newcast"] </F>
  [Text] Colombia signed a trade and economic cooperation 
agreement with 31 Caribbean countries this evening. Foreign 
Trade Minister Juan Manuel Santos explained the scope of the 
agreement. 
  [Begin Santos recording] A great opportunity has been opened 
for Colombia's productive sector because at this time we export 
to the Caribbean no more than $65 million. This is the first 
time the Caricom [Caribbean Common Market] has signed an 
agreement establishing reciprocity. In other words, we open our 
markets to them and they in turn open their markets to us. That 
had never happened before with the Caricom countries. In 
addition, this means we are fulfilling to the letter all our 
plans to open markets to Colombian products in the Latin 
American region. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

