<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Pastrana Leads Samper by 2 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Pastrana Leads Samper by 2 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1206031594 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1206031594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours Newcast"] </F>
  [Text] Andres Pastrana has a two-point lead over Ernesto 
Samper, according to a poll conducted by the National Consulting 
Center. The poll was contracted by the Bavaria company and 
released by the Caracol Network. The poll was conducted between 
2-8 June in 106 cities and municipalities. Using a copy of the 
ballot, 10,360 persons were polled. The results were as follows: 
Andres Pastrana received 49 percent support of those intending 
to vote, and Ernesto Samper received 47 percent support of those 
intending to vote. The poll's margin of error is 1.2 percent. 

</TEXT>

