<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1306140594 </F>
<F P=103> PY1306140594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Paraguay monitored through 9 
June. 
  Paraguayan Central Bank, BCP, sources have reported that the 
domestic public debt, including capital and interests, totaled 
1,364,923,000,000 guaranies by 31 December 1993. According to 
BCP records the domestic public debt by 31 December 1993, 
involving loans in guaranies and dollars, is broken down as 
follows: central government (basically the Finance Ministry): 
960.282 billion guaranies; decentralized organizations: 1.757 
billion guaranies; municipalities: 1.169 billion guaranies; and 
public enterprises, 401.715 billion guaranies. (Asuncion ABC 
COLOR in Spanish 3 Jun 94 p 20) 
  According to the Technical Planning Secretariat, a $264.7 
million trade balance deficit was reported during the first four 
months. During this period exports totaled $265.3 million, while 
imports totaled $530 million. Cotton exports declined by 41.4 
percent, and meat exports declined by 12.2 percent. Soybean 
exports grew 35 percent, coffee exports grew 77 percent, and 
timber exports grew 6.7 percent. (Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 
8 Jun 94 p 14) 

</TEXT>

