<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] After learning of the Zapatist National Liberation 
Army's rejection of the peace proposals presented by the Mexican 
Government, the Presidency of the republic issued the following 
communique: 
  In line with the will of the Mexican Government to safeguard 
peace and to obtain the economic and political development of 
the region that is in crisis, President Carlos Salinas de 
Gortari has ordered the secretaries of National Defense, 
Government, Social Development, Communication and Transport, and 
Health to continue rigorously complying with programs previously 
decided upon. 
  The communique adds: The president has ordered the National 
Defense secretary to maintain the cease-fire unilaterally 
declared on 12 January to continue patrol and relief operations 
along the country's southern border, and to conduct the 
necessary operations to prevent the smuggling of weapons into 
the region. 
  The president also ordered the commissioner for peace to 
report to the people about these specific decisions and about 
the government's decision to continue promoting peace through a 
political resolution of the conflict. 

</TEXT>

