<H3> <TI>   Salinas Willing To Mediate Cuban Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salinas Willing To Mediate Cuban Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1406045094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0001 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1406045094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Mexico City, 13 Jun (EFE) -- Today, Mexican 
President Carlos Salinas de Gortari said he is willing to 
mediate between Cuba and the United States to eliminate the 
economic embargo on the island, however, "no one has asked us to 
mediate, and we are not in the habit of going where we have not 
been invited." In a short news conference, shortly before 
leaving for Cartagena de Indias, Colombia, Salinas de Gortari 
said he is convinced the blockade solves nothing and added: "we 
believe it should be lifted and in this manner bridges for 
communication and dialogue would be built." [passage omitted] 
  The Mexican president said the visit was "very positive and 
cordial and strengthened the traditional good relations that 
exist between our two countries." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

